Sentencas: In this work, the spinel-type oxides of AFe(2)O(4) (A=Co, Ni, Cu) prepared via a glycine-nitrate process were investigated as possible cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The as prepared sample, CoFe2O4 and NiFe2O4 are cubic spinel structure, while the CuFe2O4 is tetragonal spinel structure.
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The XRD results show that AFe(2)O(4) (A=Co, Ni, Cu) is chemically compatible with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3- (LSGM) at fuel cell operation temperatures.
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At a given temperature, the order of the electrical conductivity of the ceramic samples was CuFe2O4>CoFe2O4>NiFe2O4.
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of CuFe2O4 reaches a maximum value of 2.7Scm(-1) at 850 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The order of average thermal expansion coefficient was CuFe2O4
Titulo: Electrode properties of a spinel family, AFe2O4 (A=Co, Ni, Cu), as new cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
